<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bookending the Oscar nominees for outstanding movie making are nominations for 
the ninth annual Razzie Awards heralding the year's worst films. "Cocktail," 
"Rambo III," "Hot to Trot," "Caddyshack II" and "Mack and Me" stand out among 
the bottom-of-the-heap nods given by the Golden Raspberry Award Foundation. The 
awards -- a gold spray-painted, golfball-sized raspberry atop a plastic base -- 
will be presented March 29, same day as the 61st annual Oscar ceremony. ALEENE 
MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
