<P>
MORNING REPORT: GIFTS/GRANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Blues great Willie Dixon will donate $3,000 worth of band equipment to Locke 
High School in Los Angeles next Thursday. The presentation, made through 
Dixon's Blues Heaven Foundation for the promotion and documentation of blues 
music and history, will be made in memory of blues singer Big Joe Turner. Along 
with the equipment, the school will receive a matching grant from the Yamaha 
Corp. of America. Another donation of the same value will be made Feb. 28 to 
the John P. Freeman School in Memphis, in memory of longtime Dixon associate, 
pianist Memphis Slim. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
