<P>
FUNDS FOR PALOS VERDES DRIVE WORK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rolling Hills will allocate $7,200 of the federal funds it will receive this 
fiscal year to the city of Rolling Hills Estates for reconstruction of Palos 
Verdes Drive North from Crenshaw Boulevard to Sunnyfield Drive. 
</P>
<P>
Rolling Hills, a private and gated community, cannot use the money since the 
funds may only be spent on public streets. Palos Verdes Drive North in Rolling 
Hills Estates is a principal access road to Rolling Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Plans for reconstruction of the 1 1/4-mile stretch will be put before the 
Rolling Hills Estates City Council Feb. 28. The cost of the project has not 
been set. 
