When the officers came near the two, Origel turned and wielded a .38-caliber 
handgun, pointing it at Stern and Finn, Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
Both officers pulled out their service revolvers but did not fire. They talked 
Origel into surrendering his gun without firing it, Robinson said. 
</P>
