<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO INDUSTRY NOTES: SAN DIEGO COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Martin Marietta Corp. plans to form an "advanced development and technology" 
group in San Diego, the Bethesda, Md.-based company said Wednesday. However, 
Martin Marietta has not yet leased any space or determined how many employees 
will be hired, according to a spokesman in Bethesda. 
</P>
<P>
The Martin Marietta Advanced Development &amp; Technology Operations will 
"pursue advanced technology developments across (a) broad spectrum," according 
to the spokesman. The operation will "focus primarily on new developments in 
defense electronics, missiles, astronautics and information systems," the 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Subsequent engineering and production will be handled by Martin Marietta's 
existing divisions elsewhere in the United States, the spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The new division will be directed by Robert J. Whalen, 57, a former vice 
president of Martin Marietta, who most recently was general manager of Alcoa 
Defense Systems. 
</P>
<P>
Whalen is a San Diego resident, the spokesman said. 
</P>
