<HEADLINE>
<P>
PHILHARMONIC BENEFIT CONCERT RESCHEDULED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
German conductor Christof Perick will conduct the rescheduled Los Angeles 
Philharmonic Pension Fund Benefit, Tuesday night at 8 in the Dorothy Chandler 
Pavilion. Perick will be on the podium in place of Andre Previn, the 
orchestra's music director, who is on tour with the Vienna Philharmonic. 
</P>
<P>
The concert, featuring violinist Itzhak Perlman as soloist, was rescheduled 
from Feb. 7, when Perlman suffered an ear infection. 
</P>
<P>
The program has been altered. Perlman will play the Violin Concerto by 
Beethoven, as planned, but the Dvorak symphony, originally No. 8, is now No. 9, 
"From the New World. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets for Feb. 7 will be honored. 
</P>
<P>
Information: (213) 972-7211. 
</P>
