<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: DUARTE; 
</P>
<P>
BINGO AT SCHOOL REJECTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For the second time, the school board last week rejected a request to use a 
school facility to play bingo. 
</P>
<P>
The board had agreed to review its summer decision after the Duarte Citizens 
Bingo Committee last month presented trustees with its survey that showed eight 
San Gabriel Valley schools profited from sponsoring bingo. 
</P>
<P>
The Duarte Community and Education Foundation, which raises funds for the 
school district, had been sponsoring weekly games at the City of Hope National 
Medical Center until the October, 1987, earthquake damaged the hall it was 
using. 
</P>
<P>
Supt. Bob Packer said the board denied the foundation use of a school cafeteria 
for the activity because of concerns about gambling on school grounds and the 
school's liability for the players. 
</P>
</TEXT>
