<HEADLINE>
<P>
AN UNBIASED LOOK AT GANGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This is my first letter ever written to the author of a newspaper article. 
</P>
<P>
I did so because I wish to express my appreciation for the first unbiased 
article about gang violence and use of automatic weapons. I refer to the 
article about gang problems in Pomona (Feb. 5, Times). 
</P>
<P>
It is fashionable to say "ban AK-47 assault rifles and cut gang crime." This is 
a simplistic approach to a complex problem. A gun ban will no more stop street 
violence than liquor bans stopped drinking, bans on knives stopped stabbings, 
and controls on spray cans stopped graffiti. 
</P>
<P>
Your article explored both sides of the problem. 
</P>
<P>
RICHARD HOLMSTROM 
</P>
<P>
City of Industry 
</P>
</TEXT>
