</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLY ENTERS PLAYOFFS AFTER FOURTH VICTORY OVER BIRMINGHAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Senior guard Hugo Parra scored a game-high 22 points and was perfect on nine 
field-goal attempts in leading Poly High to a 77-58 win over Birmingham in a 
City Section boys' basketball tiebreaker Wednesday at Monroe High. 
</P>
<P>
John Bruner had 15 points and 12 rebounds for Poly (11-10). The Parrots 
finished the regular season tied for second place in the East Valley League 
with Birmingham, which ended its season at 9-12. 
</P>
<P>
Juan Estrada added 18 points and 11 rebounds for Poly, which plays at Los 
Angeles High on Friday night in the first round of the 3-A Division playoffs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
