<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY COLLEGE FORFEITS MEN'S BASKETBALL GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Valley College, reduced to four players in uniform, forfeited a Western State 
Conference men's basketball game to Glendale on Wednesday at Valley. 
</P>
<P>
"It was a lousy way to win or lose," Glendale assistant Jack Giles said. 
</P>
<P>
Glendale improved to 17-11, 8-5 in conference play with two games remaining. 
Valley dropped to 17-13, 7-6. 
</P>
<P>
Valley Coach Jim Stephens was unavailable for comment. 
</P>
