<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPORTS ET CETERA: VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFFREY PARENTI MEN'S GOLF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Heidi West, who helped Francis Parker High School to three state division 1-A 
volleyball titles, said Wednesday night she will attend Georgetown University 
on a volleyball scholarship. 
</P>
<P>
West, a 6-foot-1 middle blocker, selected Georgetown over William and Mary. She 
also took trips to Virgina and Oregon State. 
</P>
<P>
"It was the hardest thing in the world," she said. "I debated for two days." 
</P>
<P>
West, a three-time all-section player, said she choose Georgetown for its 
strong academic reputation and its inner-city environment. 
</P>
<P>
"I felt it would be a bigger challenge going (to Georgetown)," she said. 
"William and Mary is in a small college town. I think after four years it might 
be too safe and too easy and become too comfortable." 
</P>
<P>
Suzy Biszantz, a right-side hitter from section 3-A runner-up Torrey Pines, 
will attend Tulane University on a volleyball scholarship. JEFFREY PARENTIMEN'S 
GOLF The University of San Diego finished first with a score of 372, Point Loma 
Nazarene (378) was second and Cal State San Bernardino (381) third in a 
nonconference tri-meet at Rancho San Diego. Andrea Strandberg of Point Loma 
Nazarene and San Bernardino's Chris Astorga and Frank Acosta tied for first 
with scores of 72.MEN'S TENNIS Sig Huber won No. 1 singles and No. 1 doubles 
matches as UC San Diego defeated Cal State Bakersfield, 7-2. Huber defeated 
Will Marino, 6-2, 6-1, and then teamed with Chris Belloli at No. 1 doubles to 
defeat Marino and David Swancott, 6-4, 6-3. UCSD is 3-2 and Cal State 
Bakersfield is 0-4. Tole Marinkovic defeated Jim Murray, 6-3, 6-3, in No. 1 
singles as San Diego State defeated Hawaii, 8-1, at SDSU. SDSU is 2-6. Hawaii 
is 8-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
