<HEADLINE>
<P>
CASTLE &amp; COOKE PROFIT JUMPS IN YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Castle &amp; Cooke Inc., the Los Angeles-based holding company for Dole Food 
Co. and Oceanic Properties Inc., Wednesday reported 1988 income from continuing 
operations of $112.3 million, up from $88.9 million in 1987. Revenue in 1988 
rose to $2.47 billion from $1.86 billion in 1987. 
</P>
<P>
For the fourth quarter of 1988, the company reported income from continuing 
operations of $19.4 million, compared to $19.3 million in the fourth quarter of 
1987. Revenue increased to $589 million from $425 million. Revenue growth in 
1988 reflects both increased sales from established company products and the 
impact of operations acquired in late 1987, the firm said. 
</P>
<P>
Dole Food Co. reported record operating results in 1988, with solid 
performances from each of its major product lines. Results from Dole's fresh 
fruit division were particularly strong. Dole's fresh vegetable operations also 
reported good results for the year. The packaged foods division showed 
substantial improvement over 1987 in all segments of its business. 
</P>
<P>
OPI which manages the company's real estate development activities, reported 
higher earnings for the year with continued sales growth among its residential 
development projects. 
</P>
