<HEADLINE>
<P>
WELLS FARGO BANK OVERCHARGED, JURY SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN FRANCISCO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A jury says Wells Fargo Bank overcharged its credit card customers $5.2 million 
in fees for making payments late and exceeding credit limits. 
</P>
<P>
The Superior Court verdict reached Tuesday, in the first of several similar 
suits against major banks, entitles holders of MasterCard and Visa cards from 
Wells Fargo between July, 1982, and May, 1987, to $4.1 million in refunds for 
late-payment fees and more than $1 million for over-limit fees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
