<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An internal investigation has been launched at Prairie View A &amp; M 
University in Prairie View, Tex., where striking football players have refused 
to return to the field until the head coach is fired. 
</P>
<P>
Percy Pierre, Prairie View A&amp;M's president, announced the investigation 
after meeting privately with 55 of the striking football players who have 
claimed the football coach is blocking their education. 
</P>
<P>
Players, who began their strike last week, also have charged that Coach Haney 
Catchings has put them through unsafe drills, held frequent six-hour practices 
and threatened to suspend scholarship funds if athletes did not produce on the 
field. 
</P>
</TEXT>
