<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A rape charge against shortstop Jose Uribe of the San Francisco Giants was 
dismissed in Santo Domingo in the Dominican Republic. 
</P>
<P>
Uribe, 29, was accused by a woman of drugging her, threatening her with a gun 
and raping her. He had denied the charge. 
</P>
<P>
The dismissal of the case was recommended by Jose Francisco Rodriguez, district 
attorney at the province of San Cristobal. 
</P>
<P>
"There is no reason to indict or bring him to prison because there is no 
guilt," said Rodriguez. 
</P>
