<HEADLINE>
<P>
WAGNER BEATS ROMEO IN BOWLING FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lisa Wagner, of Palmetto, Fla., the 1988 woman bowler of the year, defeated 
top-seeded Robin Romeo of Van Nuys, 266-182, Wednesday night to win the $35,000 
Ladies Pro Bowlers Tour Lady LaMode Open at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
Wagner won her 22nd career title along with the $7,000 first prize. She 
advanced to the championship match by first defeating Rene Fleming of Oklahoma 
City, 219-214. 
</P>
<P>
Romeo, who won last week's tournament at Canoga Park, earned $3,500 for second 
place. 
</P>
<P>
Betty Morris of Stockton started the championship round with a 247-226 victory 
over Cheryl Daniels of Detroit. Morris then defeated Paula Drake of Broken 
Arrow, Okla., 247-203, before losing to Fleming, 225-202. 
</P>
<P>
Fleming won $2,000 for third place. Morris earned $1,750 for fourth, Drake 
$1,500 for fifth and Daniels $1,400 for sixth. 
</P>
<P>
LPBT's next stop is the $30,000 San Diego tournament, which begins Saturday at 
Kearny Mesa Bowl in San Diego. 
</P>
</TEXT>
