<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC TO PLAY HOST TO UC IRVINE TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN WEYLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
STOCKTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UC Irvine, which has won three of its last four games, will face the University 
of the Pacific, which has a nine-game losing streak, at 7:30 tonight in a Big 
West Conference basketball game in the Spanos Center. 
</P>
<P>
Pacific has won only once in 11 Big West games and has a 5-16 overall record. 
Irvine (9-12, 6-6) beat the Tigers, 90-88, Jan. 21 when center Mike Doktorczyk 
made all 12 shots from the floor and scored 28 points. Doktorczyk is hampered 
by a severe thigh bruise, but probably will play tonight. 
</P>
<P>
The Anteaters' new inside threat, Ricky Butler, scored 20 or more for three 
consecutive games before being triple-teamed by Cal State Fullerton Saturday 
night. He was held to 13 points as Irvine lost, 78-75. JOHN WEYLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA021689-0159 </DOCNO>
