<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO MOVE WEST, SAYS RATHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dan Rather, while discussing CBS' increased emphasis on coverage of Japan and 
the Pacific Rim, was asked if he thought the day might come when a network news 
program such as his would move West permanently to better cover the East. 
</P>
<P>
It's unlikely, he said, although "I've urged us to do this for years, to move 
to Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
"But I'm the only person around there who believes it's a practical idea," he 
added. "Some people laugh at me, and others call for the guys in the white 
coats from Bellevue." 
</P>
<P>
Relocating from New York doesn't seem to be in the cards, he said, noting that 
it would cost a lot of money. Another important reason: New York is still the 
home of the networks' parent corporations. 
</P>
<P>
"Power," he said, "is in direct proportion to proximty.....With the corporate 
network headquarters in New York, it makes a lot of sense for the news 
divisions, all three, to remain headquartered there." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
RATHER, DAN; CBS TELEVISION NETWORK; NEWS MEDIA; TELEVISION BROADCASTS; 
TELEVISION NETWORKS; RELOCATION OF BUSINESS; CORPORATIONS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
