ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
MAN FATALLY SHOOTS WIFE, SELF AT MOTEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Fullerton man, reportedly despondent over unsuccessful attempts to reconcile 
with his wife, fatally shot her and then himself after an argument, police said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Anaheim Police Sgt. Chet Barry said Carlos Melendez, 31, went to the Travelodge 
motel in the 1700 block of East Katella Avenue about 9:30 p.m. Monday to see 
his wife, Sandra Melendez, 29, the hotel's night clerk. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said they heard the Melendezes, who had recently separated, arguing 
in the hotel's office, and then three shots. 
</P>
<P>
Barry said that Carlos Melendez, a wire assembler for Datum Inc. in Anaheim, 
shot his wife twice in the chest with a revolver, then shot himself once in the 
head. 
</P>
</TEXT>
