<P>
SANTA ANA VALLEY RALLIES, BUT CAN'T OVERTAKE GAHR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a game dominated by turnovers, Gahr High School built a small lead over 
Santa Ana Valley and then held on for a 84-79 victory Wednesday in the first 
round of the Division 5-A Southern Section playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
Before a sparse crowd at Gahr, Santa Ana Valley (12-12) fell behind by nine 
points, 44-35, at halftime and then pulled to within two points late in the 
third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
But Gahr (17-8), which committed 21 turnovers, built an 11-point lead midway 
through the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
The Falcons came back again, pulling within 80-76 with 1:10 left. But a layup 
by Rod Summers and two free throws by Mark Charbonnet put the game away. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana Valley, which committed 18 turnovers, was led by Bryan Singleton with 
25 points and Chuck Steen with 23 points. Eddie Martinez scored 20 points to 
lead Gahr, which will play at Irvine Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View 56, Dana Hills 52 -- Ted Pelonis scored the final five points as the 
Seahawks (18-8) held a second-half rally at Ocean View. 
</P>
<P>
Pelonis hit two free throws with 22 seconds left in the game to clinch the 
victory after Dana Hills pulled within two, 54-52. Pelonis finished with 15 
points. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Fedden scored 10 of his 18 points in the third quarter as Dana Hills cut a 
30-22 halftime deficit to 42-39. 
</P>
<P>
Dana Hills (15-14) outscored Ocean View, 6-2, at the start of the fourth 
quarter to take a 45-44 lead. But Todd Norman, who had 21 points, hit two free 
throws to give Ocean View the lead for good, 46-45, with 5:14 left. 
</P>
