<TEXT>
<P>
The Paramount Unified School District has offered teachers a 2% salary 
increase, Supt. Richard B. Caldwell said. In a Feb. 9 story about teacher 
contract negotiations in several Southeast school districts, The Times 
incorrectly reported that the Paramount district had offered its teachers a 5% 
salary increase. Caldwell said a 5% salary increase already has been accepted 
by classified and management employees. Negotiations with teachers remain at an 
impasse. 
