COLUMBIA ALUMINUM ACQUIRES INDAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GOLDENDALE, Wash. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Columbia Aluminum announced today it has purchased two Southern California 
companies, Indal Aluminum and Indal Aluminum Products, for an undisclosed 
price. 
</P>
<P>
Kenneth Peterson Jr., Columbia Aluminum's chief executive officer, said the 
plants will continue operations in Columbia's name through a new subsidiary -- 
Columbia Pacific Aluminum Corp. 
</P>
<P>
Indal Aluminum is located in the City of Industry. Indal Aluminum Products is 
in the City of Commerce. 
</P>
<P>
"Columbia's California operations will continue in their current markets and 
will focus on customer service both to retain existing customers and expand 
sales activities to obtain new customers," Peterson said. "Our goal is to be 
clearly the best in the Western extrusion market." 
</P>
<P>
Columbia Aluminum of Goldendale is a primary aluminum smelter that is partially 
owned by its employees. 
</P>
<P>
Peterson also announced the appointment of Norval Prakash as president and 
chief operating officer of Columbia Pacific Aluminum Corp., which will be 
headquartered in the City of Industry. 
</P>
